A man accused of stealing Sh5,000 has been granted a Sh500,000 bond or Sh200,000 cash bail by a Chuka court.Felix Kinyua is accused of strangling Isaac Mutithi before stealing a wallet containing Sh5,000, a national ID and NHIF card, among other valuables from the victim.He denied the charges and was directed to return for hearing on January 19.Chief resident magistrate Mwanamkuu Sudi also said the accused will be given a lawyer by the State as he cannot afford one.The matter will be mentioned on February 13.